Sentencas: Thin films of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte were prepared by atomic layer deposition at 300 degrees C for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications.
Titulo: Electrical properties of thin yttria-stabilized zirconia overlayers produced by atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: YSZ samples of 300-1000 nm thickness were deposited onto La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) cathodes.
Titulo: Electrical properties of thin yttria-stabilized zirconia overlayers produced by atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: A microstructural study was performed on these samples and their electrical properties were characterised between 100 and 390 degrees C by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Electrical properties of thin yttria-stabilized zirconia overlayers produced by atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: A remarkable feature is that the as-deposited layers were already crystalline without any annealing treatment.
Titulo: Electrical properties of thin yttria-stabilized zirconia overlayers produced by atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Their resistance decreased when reducing the layer thickness; nevertheless, their Conductivity and activation energy were significantly lower than those reported in the literature for bulk YSZ.
Titulo: Electrical properties of thin yttria-stabilized zirconia overlayers produced by atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cell applications
